Anthraquinones are abundant in plants, lichens and fungi, with more than 700 examples in the literature (
Fouillaud et al., 2016
). Anthraquinones have been shown to possess biological activities like cytotoxic, antimicrobial, and anti-diabetic activities, and are also applied in the dyeing industry (
Ayo et al., 2007
; 
Duval et al., 2016
; 
Lee and Sohn, 2008
). Anthraquinones have been reported from the 

Colletotrichum

genus before; several anthraquinones from the endophytic fungus 

Colletotrichum
sp.

JS-0367 possessed significant neuroprotective activity (
Song et al., 2018
). Bianthrones are a class of compound formed by fusion of two anthrone precursors. Much rarer than the anthraquinones, these compounds have been reported in plants, animals and fungi (
Ji et al., 2014
). The naturally-occurring bianthrones tend to be substituted by methyl, hydroxy, methoxy groups, and occasionally more complex substituents. Studies have shown that bianthrones can exhibit potent biological activity, for example cytotoxicity against a range of cancer cell lines (
Mandelare et al., 2018
; 
Song et al., 2018
), antifungal properties (
Elbanna et al., 2021
), and antiplasmodial activity against 

Plasmodium falciparum
(
Ndjakou Lenta et al., 2008
)

. While the biosynthesis of anthraquinones have been well-studied in several fungi (
Chiang et al., 2010
), the biosynthesis of bianthrones has been far less well studied in microbes. The ratios of stereoisomers produced in the current study is consistent with a non-stereospecific dimerization mechanism, though whether this is enzyme catalyzed or spontaneous is unknown.

After fermentation, the fungal culture in each flask was first filtered through cheesecloth, the broth was extracted with EtOAc (400 mL) three times, while the mycelium was extracted with MeOH (200 mL) under ultrasonication. Then the EtOAc extracts and MeOH extracts were combined together and reduced under vacuum to yield a crude extract (
8.73 g
). To remove polar media components, aqueous-organic solvent partitions was conducted on the crude extract using EtOAc and BuOH in turn; the organic fractions were then combined and concentrated under vacuum (Savant SC 210A, Ameritech) to yield an organic-soluble extract (
2.85 g
).

Diffraction intensity was collected at 159.99 (10) K on a Rigaku XtaLAB FRX Diffractometer equipped with a Hypix6000HE detector, using Cu Kα radiation (λ = 1.54184 Å). Data reduction was accomplished using program crysAlispro (version 1.171. 
35.45 g
). The structure was solved by intrinsic phasing method using SHELXT and was refined by full-matrix least-squares technique using SHELXL-2015 embedded into OLEX2 1.3. All non-H atoms were refined with anisotropic displacement parameters. H atoms were placed in calculated positions and were refined using a riding model with an isotropic displacement parameter.
